# RoboLedger V5.2.6: Popout Grid & Ref# Syncing

Implementing advanced UI features for grid detachment and dynamic account renaming.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Popout Strategy**: I will use the "Object URL" (Blob) strategy to serve the popped-out grid. This allows for zero-configuration detachment without needing separate server-side files, maintaining the same styles and Tabulator logic as the main app.

## Proposed Changes

### Ref# Input & Pill Syncing (app.js)
- **handleRefUpdate**: Update logic to ensure `window.render()` is called after a successful rename, which will automatically update the account switcher pills since they use `acc.ref || acc.name`.

### Grid Popout System (app.js)
- **window.popOutGrid**: 
  - Serialize current grid data and styles.
  - Generate a `Blob` containing a full HTML document (Tabulator CDN, styles, and data).
  - Open a new window via `URL.createObjectURL(blob)`.
  - Set up a `postMessage` listener in the main window to receive updates from the child.
- **Child Window Logic**:
  - Render a full-screen Tabulator grid.
  - Send messages back to `window.opener` on cell edits or row deletions.
  - Implement a "Dock" button to close the window and signal the parent to re-render.
- **Heartbeat Monitor**: Use `setInterval` to detect when the popup is closed manually, automatically restoring the local grid.

### UI Enhancements
- **Missing Grid Overlay**: When the grid is popped out, replace the local `.grid-container-wall` content with an informative overlay: "Grid Popped Out • [Bring it Back]".

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Pill Sync**: Rename a Ref# and verify the pill updates immediately on Enter/Blur.
2. **Popout**: Click the "Popout" button. A separate window should open with the same data.
3. **Edit Sync**: Edit a cell in the popout window. Verify the main ledger state updates (can verify by docking or checking console).
4. **Docking**: Close the popout window. Verify the main window grid restores instantly.
